ZH: 这些小问题可以置之度外。
EN: These minor issues can be disregarded.

ZH: 她对外界的批评总是置之度外。
EN: She always brushes off criticism from the outside.

ZH: 他常常因为太过专注于自己的目标而将其他事情置之度外。
EN: He often neglects other matters because he is too focused on his goals.

ZH: 请不要把我的话置之度外，这是很重要的建议。
EN: Please do not disregard what I said, it is an important advice.

ZH: 尽管遇到了一些困难，他依然置之度外，继续前行。
EN: Despite facing some challenges, he disregarded them and continued moving forward.

ZH: 面对失败，他选择了将它置之度外，重新开始。
EN: Faced with failure, he chose to disregard it and start over.

ZH: 请置之度外我的意见，做出你自己的决定。
EN: Disregard my opinion and make your own decision.

ZH: 我们应该把过去的纠纷置之度外，共同合作解决问题。
EN: We should set aside past disputes and work together to solve the problem.

ZH: 面对这种负面情绪，我们应该学会将其置之度外。
EN: Faced with this negative emotion, we should learn to disregard it.

ZH: 他总是会将周围的一切置之度外，专注于自己的工作。
EN: He always disregards everything around him and focuses on his work.

ZH: 别太在意别人的看法，将其置之度外即可。
EN: Don't pay too much attention to what others think, just disregard it.

ZH: 当你遇到嘈杂的环境时，尽可能地将其置之度外。
EN: When you encounter a noisy environment, try to disregard it as much as possible.

ZH: 对于那些无关紧要的事情，我们可以将其置之度外。
EN: For those irrelevant matters, we can disregard them.

ZH: 他的反对意见被大家置之度外，决定已经做出。
EN: His objections were disregarded by everyone and the decision had been made.

ZH: 不要因为曾经的失败而气馁，应该将其置之度外，重新来过。
EN: Don't be discouraged by past failures, set them aside and start over.

ZH: 我们应该把猜测和推测置之度外，通过事实来做判断。
EN: We should disregard speculation and conjecture and base our judgments on facts.

ZH: 这些不和谐的声音可以置之度外，不用过多在意。
EN: These discordant voices can be disregarded, no need to pay too much attention.

ZH: 当你的内心感到困扰时，尽量将其置之度外，寻求解决之道。
EN: When you feel troubled inside, try your best to disregard it and seek a solution.

ZH: 尽管面对挫折，但我们不应该将其置之度外，应该从中汲取教训。
EN: Despite setbacks, we should not disregard them, but draw lessons from them.

ZH: 当别人的意见与你相悖时，你可以置之度外，坚持自己的立场。
EN: When others' opinions contradict yours, you can disregard them and stick to your own position.
